Coming back after a 2 year recovery from ACL surgery has been a process. 

This new stage of my life competing on the world stage has been amazing. I completely started from scratch and made some changes to my team. I’ve added the legendary coach @eddiebravo10p as my head jujitsu coach, got a new chef in @theknockoutbakery, went back to the best sport’s doctor in the business @teamdrg ,last but not least, I needed a new mental coach. 
So I added @samantonen, Sam has multiple Adcc world champions and I’m about to get added to that list. 

Your mental game is more important then lifting. You need to believe that you’re the best in the world before you step on the mat. As athletes we invest in the new gear, strength and conditioning coaches and more, but need to remember, when you step on the mat or field, it’s you and your mind against the world. 

Invest in your mental game. 
Ian Butler 

#mentalhealth
